issue.title: transcripts are cluttered with metadata and hard to read
issue.body:
Currently each message in a transcript takes up 10 lines and includes: message & conversation ID, cell # and device type, read by user: true/false, sent by client: true/false, the case manager's name, status, date created, date transcript downloaded, and local timezone.

We should figure out which metadata are critical and remove everything else, and reduce repetition for elements that don't/rarely change.

In Multnomah, swap SO with SWIS
issue.body: A Multnomah County PO requested when he's adding a new client, he can add the SWIS (state-wide information system) ID. Since the SO# input isn't relevant, he requested to remove that field and add a SWIS input instead.

issue.title: For Multnomah, swap SID with OTN
issue.body:
In Multnomah County, they have SIDs (state IDs) instead of OTNs. POs have requested that we remove the OTN input and include a SID input when they add a new client.

Not sure what this would do to the data structure, so let me know how easy / difficult it would be to deploy this. If it's easy to do, I know POs would appreciate it!
